From: Namecoin Integration <namecoin-integration@example.com>
Date: 2026-04-16
Subject: [PATCH 3/4] netwerk/dns: Add nsNamecoinResolver class

Adds nsNamecoinResolver.h and nsNamecoinResolver.cpp to netwerk/dns/,
implementing native Namecoin (.bit) domain resolution via ElectrumX.

This is Phase 1: DNS resolution only (A/AAAA records from blockchain).
No TLS/DANE validation yet (Phase 2).

Architecture overview:
  - nsNamecoinResolver::Resolve() dispatches to background thread pool
  - ResolveInternal() drives the full resolution pipeline:
      1. Compute ElectrumX scripthash (OP_NAME_UPDATE index script + SHA-256)
      2. Query blockchain.scripthash.get_history
      3. Pick most recent confirmed tx
      4. Query blockchain.transaction.get (verbose)
      5. Check current block height (expiry: >36,000 blocks)
      6. Decode NAME_UPDATE output → JSON value
      7. Parse ip/ip6/alias/translate/map fields
      8. Follow alias chain (max hops via pref)
      9. Convert addresses to NetAddr
      10. Compute cache TTL from remaining blocks
  - ElectrumXRequest() uses nsIWebSocketChannel (Gecko's WS stack)
  - SHA-256 via NSS HASH_HashBuf

Static helpers exposed for testing:
  - ComputeScripthash(name) → ElectrumX scripthash hex
  - DecodeNameScript(hex) → name + value strings
  - IsNamecoinHost(hostname) → bool
  - ParseNameValue(json, hostname) → NamecoinNameValue

Also adds nsNamecoinResolver to netwerk/dns/moz.build.

Key correctness note:
  The scripthash computation MUST use OP_NAME_UPDATE (0x53). Using
  OP_NAME_SHOW (0xd1) produces empty query results — silent failure.
  Verified against electrumx.testls.space for d/testls and d/bitcoin.

Reference implementation:
  tls-namecoin-ext/background/electrumx-ws.js (JavaScript)
  tls-namecoin-ext/background/namecoin-resolver.js (JavaScript)

